properties.areaDesc: Lake Superior from Saxon Harbor WI to Upper Entrance to Portage Canal MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian border including Isle Royal National Park; Lake Superior west of a line from Saxon Harbor WI to Grand Portage MN beyond 5NM; Lake Superior from Upper Entrance to Portage Canal to Manitou Island MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian Border
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued February 10 at 10:12AM EST until February 12 at 5:00AM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
waves 6 to 11 feet possible.

* WHERE...Lake Superior west of a line from Saxon Harbor WI to
Grand Portage MN beyond 5NM, Lake Superior from Upper Entrance
to Portage Canal to Manitou Island MI 5NM off shore to the
US/Canadian Border and Lake Superior from Saxon Harbor WI to
Upper Entrance to Portage Canal MI 5NM off shore to the
US/Canadian border including Isle Royale National Park.

* WHEN...From Tuesday afternoon through late Tuesday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM TUESDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE TUESDAY NIGHT
